name: Crispy Baked Parmesan Garlic Edamame
author: Culinary Envy
summary: Crispy baked Parmesan garlic edamame is an absolutely delicious sweet/salty high-protein snack. Store in an airtight container and enjoy!
ingredients: ¼ teaspoon chile powder with lime (such as Trader Joe's® Chile Lime Seasoning Blend)
1 pinch salt and freshly ground black pepper
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Toss edamame and garlic olive oil in a bowl to coat completely
Mix Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, onion powder, chile lime seasoning, salt, and pepper in a separate bowl
Add to the edamame mixture and toss until well combined
Spread edamame in 1 layer on a rimmed baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until Parmesan cheese begins to brown, turning once halfway through, 10 to 15 minutes
